# OpenTrade CODEOWNERS
#
# Per rule 70 and ADR-0018 D10. Phase 0 is solo-developed by the
# founder, so every path resolves to @skyyuch. The granular path-
# specific entries below are intentionally present (even though they
# all point to the same owner today) so that when a second contributor
# joins, sensitive areas can be re-routed in a single targeted PR
# rather than a large reshuffle.
#
# Reviewer assignment via CODEOWNERS is automatic. Branch protection
# rules (configured in the GitHub Settings UI per ADR-0018 D10) make
# CODEOWNERS-suggested reviewers a hard requirement on PRs to main.

# ── Default fallback ────────────────────────────────────────────────
* @skyyuch

# ── High-sensitivity areas (Phase 1+ will add @security-advisor) ────
# Smart contracts — financial primitives. Phase 1+ ships
# ReviewRegistry.sol; per ADR-0015 D5, that PR also tightens solhint
# and likely adds a security-focused reviewer.
/packages/contracts/ @skyyuch

# Security rule itself — never change without explicit founder review.
/.cursor/rules/50-security.mdc @skyyuch

# Architecture decisions — every ADR change is a "future you will
# regret" filter (per docs/decisions/README.md). Founder gates all.
/docs/decisions/ @skyyuch

# Cursor rules — operational discipline for every AI agent in the
# repo. Changes touch how the project enforces its red lines.
/.cursor/rules/ @skyyuch

# AWS account / IaC boundary — anything here is a real cloud cost.
/infra/terraform/ @skyyuch

# CI/CD workflows + Dependabot — supply-chain surface.
/.github/ @skyyuch

# Database schema + migrations — destructive changes possible.
/packages/db/prisma/ @skyyuch
